Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Thinly slice the @tomato{1}. Thinly slice the @mushrooms{125%g}.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the mushrooms and cook until charred, ~{3-4%minutes}, shifting
occasionally.

Once cooked, season lightly with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then
transfer to a #bowl{}.

== Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, mix together half the @chopped tomatoes{1/2%pack} and
@?sugar{1/2%tbsp}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.
You've made your base sauce!

== Assembly ==

Use a #spoon{} to spread the sauce over each of the @flatbread base{2}, leaving
a 1cm border around the edge (for the crust). Scatter the
@grated cheese{100%g} over the top.

Top the pizzas with the charred mushrooms and @Serrano ham{65%g} slices.

Carefully pop your pizzas onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Bake in the oven until the cheese has melted and is bubbling, ~{10-14%minutes}.

Remove the pizzas from the oven and cut into slices.

Top with the sliced tomato.